          "answer": "Crisis assistance covers shut-off notices, broken heating equipment, lack of fuel, or other energy emergencies. You'll need documentation like a disconnection notice or repair estimate. Crisis grants can go up to $10,000 compared to regular heating assistance maximum of $2,561."
